## Connecting to Instances

```bash
# Standard SSH (key pair)
ssh -i ~/.ssh/mykey.pem ubuntu@<public-ip>

# SSH via SSM (no public IP needed, no open port 22)
aws ssm start-session --target i-1234567890abcdef0

# SSH tunnel through SSM (port forwarding)
aws ssm start-session \
  --target i-1234567890abcdef0 \
  --document-name AWS-StartPortForwardingSession \
  --parameters '{"portNumber":["5432"],"localPortNumber":["5432"]}'
```

SSM Session Manager is the modern way to access instances. No bastion host needed, no port 22 open, full audit trail in CloudTrail.

