## Instance Lifecycle

```bash
# Stop (preserves EBS, stops billing for compute)
aws ec2 stop-instances --instance-ids i-xxxxxxxx

# Start
aws ec2 start-instances --instance-ids i-xxxxxxxx

# Reboot (stays running, OS-level restart)
aws ec2 reboot-instances --instance-ids i-xxxxxxxx

# Terminate (DELETES the instance and root EBS by default)
aws ec2 terminate-instances --instance-ids i-xxxxxxxx

# Protect from accidental termination
aws ec2 modify-instance-attribute \
  --instance-id i-xxxxxxxx \
  --disable-api-termination
```

