## User Data — Bootstrap Scripts

User data runs once when the instance first launches. Use it to install software, pull configs, register with a service.

```bash
aws ec2 run-instances \
  --image-id ami-0xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx \
  --instance-type t3.micro \
  --user-data file://bootstrap.sh \
  ...
```

```bash
# bootstrap.sh
#!/bin/bash
set -euxo pipefail

apt-get update -y
apt-get install -y nginx
systemctl enable nginx
systemctl start nginx

echo "Server: $(hostname)" > /var/www/html/index.html
```

Logs from user data: `/var/log/cloud-init-output.log`

