## Key Insight for DevOps

Security groups are the most common source of "why can't my app connect to X" in AWS. Before assuming it's an application problem, always verify the security group allows the traffic on the exact port and from the exact source. Use `nc -zv hostname port` from inside the instance to test.

Never open port 22 to `0.0.0.0/0` in production. Use SSM Session Manager instead — it requires no inbound ports and gives you a full audit trail.